In some cases, cardinality bounds come from the KB itself. For instance, Wikidata uses the single-value constraint\footnote{Single-valued constraint definition in Wikidata: \url{https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Help:Property_constraints_portal/Single_value}.} for predicates with exactly one object\footnote{An element can have only one atomic number \url{https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P1086}.}. However, such cases are rare.